Triangle $VWR$ is one of these triangles, so its area is $\frac14.$ But the area of parallelogram $UVRW$ is twice the area of triangle $VWR.$ Thus, parallelogram $UVRW$ has an area of $\frac14 \times 2 = \boxed{\frac12}.$

